3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The proposed framework aims to enhance the performance of the cloud infrastructure, which involves control and management of the system. 
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes an algorithm for resource allocation, which falls under the domain of software engineering. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Although the paper does not explicitly discuss security, the allocation of resources in a cloud environment involves ensuring the security and privacy of user data, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security.
